checkPrime(numbers);
```

This function uses a nested loop to check if each number in the array is a prime number. It first checks if the number is less than 2 (which is not considered a prime number). If it is not less than 2, it checks if the number is divisible by any number between 2 and the square root of the number. If the number is not divisible by any of these numbers, it is considered a prime number. If a prime number is found, it will print the number to the console.

